# Pigment — architecture & conventions

Stack: **Next.js 16 App Router · TypeScript · Tailwind v4 · shadcn/ui · Base UI
(`@base-ui/react`) · Supabase (`@supabase/ssr`) · Vercel · Vitest.** Read
`node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using Next APIs — this version has breaking changes.

## Structure & ownership (the 100+-team model)
- `components/ui/*`, `lib/`, `app/globals.css`, `.cursor/` — **platform team** (design system + gates).
- `app/campaigns/*`, `components/campaigns/*` — **a product team** (consumes the system).
- Ownership is enforced by `CODEOWNERS`; don't blur the boundary.

## Rendering
- Default to **Server Components**; fetch data in `lib/` from RSCs. Mark only interactive
  files `'use client'` (theme, filter, anything with state/handlers).
- Server Supabase client uses async `cookies()` with `getAll`/`setAll` (`setAll` wrapped in
  try/catch for read-only RSC contexts).

## Conventions
- Tokens/system components only — see `.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc`.
- Keep `npm test`, `npm run typecheck`, and `npm run build` green on `main`.
- Smallest change that satisfies the request + its test. No speculative abstractions.
- Never write `.env*`; never inline secrets; never call the network from client components.

## Agent permissions (editor vs headless)
The allow/deny posture is enforced deterministically by the `beforeShellExecution` hook
(`.cursor/hooks/guard-shell.sh`) — it fires in the editor, the `cursor` CLI, and cloud/CI
agents. Policy is **context-split**:
- **Editor / local chat:** allow `git add`, `commit`, `push`, `pull` (ship from chat); deny
  destructive git (`reset`, `clean`, force push, `branch -D`), `rm -rf`, writes to `.env*`, and
  outbound `curl`/`wget`.
- **CI / headless (`GITHUB_ACTIONS` / `CI=true`):** deny **all** git shell — workflow steps
  own commit/push (INJURY B demo). Agent may still edit files under `app/**` /
  `components/**` / `lib/**` and run `npm test` / `typecheck` / `build`.
